Kisumu Central MP aspirant Richard Ogendo has said he will only accept the ODM nominations results if defeated fairly.He said rigging will not be tolerated in Kisumu county and those planning to do so will be in for a rude shock.Ogendo, while popularising his bid yesterday, called on the county elections board to ensure free, fair and credible primaries set for April 24.He said his campaigns are focussed on empowerment through use of talents and sports and the creation of opportunities. Ogendo has donated 20 shoe shine shades to traders to increase their income. He said the leadership belongs to the people and they should be allowed to elect leaders of their choice.